02/06/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece ranks among the EU states that spend large amounts of their budget on border protection and tightening border control, according to Minister of Public Order Michalis Chrisochoidis. Speaking Saturday (31 May), he said Greece spends over 600m euros annually on border protection. He added that at the EU summit in Thessaloniki later this month, Athens plans to present a proposal under which such costs would be shared equally by all EU members. (MPA - 31/05/03)
